      <ROUTINE ID='routine_2054' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03 session_40 session_60' SECURITY_REFS='security_level_2'>
        <NAME>Height sensors calibration</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0x2054</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION>Routine required by Service and for End of Line

Audience - Technician End of Line Development</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>200</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>1.      Verify preconditions are met. 

a.              Vehicle on level ground

b.              All doors/decklid closed

c.              No occupants present 

d.              Ignition in RUN position (provides power to VDM)

e.              Fuel level estimated in DID 0xDE05 or available via CAN signal (FuelLvl_Pc_Dsply)

f.              DID 0xDE07 (Calibration Offset Required Configuration) set to 0x00 (Calibration Offset Required)  if you want the calibration offset to be applied, else set to 0xFF (Calibration Offset Not Required) 

g.              Neutralized suspension 

        

2.      Diagnostic preconditons 

a.              DTC 0x512455 shall be present – indicating that sensors have not been calibrated or require calibration (this precondition need not be present when recalibrating due to service)

b.              The following DTC codes pertaining to CCD module shall not be present: 

i.                          0x5A0311    Left Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

ii.                         0x5A0312    Left Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

iii.                        0x5A0411    Right Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

iv.                         0x5A0412    Right Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

v.                          0x5A0511    Left Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

vi.                         0X5A0512    Left Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

vii.                        0x5A0611    Right Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

viii.                       0x5A0612    Right Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

c.              In addition to the height sensor DTCs above, if CalConfg_B_WhlSpdEnbl = 1, the following DTCs shall also not be present:

i.                          0x510C11    Left Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Ground

ii.                         0x510C12    Left Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Battery

iii.                        0x510C13    Left Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Open

iv.                         0x510C64    Left Front Damper Solenoid  - Signal Plausibility Failure

v.                          0x510D11    Right Front Damper Solenoid - Circuit Short to Ground

vi.                         0x510D12    Right Front Damper Solenoid - Circuit Short to Battery

vii.                        0x510D13    Right Front Damper Solenoid - Circuit Open

viii.                       0x510D64    Right Front Damper Solenoid - Signal Plausibility Failure

ix.                         0x510E11    Left Rear Damper Solenoid   - Circuit Short to Ground

x.                          0x510E12    Left Rear Damper Solenoid   - Circuit Short to Battery

xi.                         0x510E13    Left Rear Damper Solenoid   - Circuit Open

xii.                        0x510E64    Left Rear Damper Solenoid   - Signal Plausibility Failure

xiii.                       0x510F11    Right Rear Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Ground

xiv.                        0x510F12    Right Rear Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Battery

xv.                         0x510F13    Right Rear Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Open

xvi.                        0x510F64    Right Rear Damper Solenoid  - Signal Plausibility Failure

d.              Module shall be in Extended Diagnostic Session (session 0x03)

e.              Module shall be unlocked via Diagnostic Service 0x27 (Security Access) to Security Level 0x03.

 

3.      Upon passing Preconditions Test, the operator will send Diagnostic Service 0x31, Routine Control, SubFunction 0x01, start Routine, Routine 0x2054, Height Sensor Calibration. Suspension position sensor voltages can be read from Vehicle Dynamics Control Module (module ID: 0x721). The DID values corresponding to wheel ends are as follows:

a.              3B70 = LF suspension position sensor voltage

b.              3B71 = RF suspension position sensor voltage

c.              3B72 = LR suspension position sensor voltage

d.              3B73 = RR suspension position sensor voltage

 

4.      At calibration, the vehicle should be at plant curb loading. At this time, these suspension voltage values do not correspond to zero suspension position as they need to be adjusted for fuel level.  Any voltage that reads lower than the adjusted zero position voltage shall represent a positive (rebound) suspension position value. Any voltage that reads higher than adjusted zero position voltage shall represent a negative (jounce) suspension position value.

 

5.      If height sensor voltage are not within the range defined by the curb portions of the Height Sensor Calibration Range – Front (0xDE09) and Height Sensor Calibration Range – Rear (0xDE10) DIDs calibration shall fail and update Height Sensor Calibration DIDs 205E, 205F, 2060 or 2061 based on the faulted corner(s).</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
        <EXIT_CONDITIONS>Transitioning to any session will cause the routine results to be lost</EXIT_CONDITIONS>

          <ROUTINE_RESPONSE_PARAMETERS>
            <ROUTINE_PARAM>
              <NAME>RoutineInfo</NAME>
              <BYTE_SIZE>1</BYTE_SIZE>

                <DATA_DEFINITION>

                </DATA_DEFINITION>
              </SUB_FIELD>
              <SUB_FIELD ID='routine_2054_subfield_2'>

                <LEAST_SIG_BIT>0</LEAST_SIG_BIT>

                <DATA_DEFINITION>
                  <DATA_TYPE>enumerated</DATA_TYPE>

      <ROUTINE ID='routine_F000' SERVICE_REFS='service_31' SESSION_REFS='session_03 session_40 session_60' SECURITY_REFS='security_level_2'>
        <NAME>OBS Calibration Data</NAME>
        <NUMBER>0xF000</NUMBER>
        <DESCRIPTION> Data storage of OBS data into VDM NVM via DE DIDs</DESCRIPTION>
        <MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>200</MAX_ROUTINE_RUN_TIME>
        <RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>no</RESTART_WHILE_RUNNING>
        <ENTRY_CONDITIONS>1.    Preconditions

The following conditions must be met before calibration procedure may begin are listed below. Manually checked preconditions shall be checked included in the Part 2 as Special Procedures.

 

a.      Manually Checked Preconditions

i.              Vehicle on level ground

ii.             All doors/decklid closed

iii.            Ignition in RUN position (provides power to VDM)

iv.             Fuel level estimated in DID 0xDE05 or available via CAN signal (FuelLvl_Pc_Dsply)

v.              Neutralized suspension   

 

b.      VDM Checked Preconditions

i.              The following DTC codes pertaining to VDM module shall not be present: 

-                           0x5A0311    Left Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

-                           0x5A0312    Left Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

-                           0x5A0411    Right Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

-                           0x5A0412    Right Front Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

-                           0x5A0511    Left Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

-                           0X5A0512    Left Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

-                           0x5A0611    Right Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Ground

-                           0x5A0612    Right Rear Height Sensor Circuit Short to Battery

ii.             In addition to the height sensor DTCs above, if the vehicle has CCD, the following DTCs shall also not be present:

-                           0x510C11    Left  Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Ground

-                           0x510C12    Left  Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Battery

-                           0x510C13    Left  Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Open

-                           0x510C64    Left  Front Damper Solenoid  - Signal Plausibility Failure

-                           0x510D11    Right Front Damper Solenoid  - Circuit Short to Ground

iv.             Module shall be unlocked via Diagnostic Service 0x27 (Security Access) to Security Level 0x03.

v.              Ignition_Status =  RUN 

vi.             9V &lt; Vcc &lt; 16 V

vii.            Vehicle Speed &lt; 0.5 kph

 

2.    Routine procedure

 

a.      Curb

i.              Record the measured wheel weight of all four wheels individually while the vehicle is completely unloaded with the possible exemption of a driver in the vehicle.

ii.             Without adjusting the load on the vehicle, send Diagnostic Service 0x31, Routine Control, SubFunction 0x01, start Routine, Routine 0xF000 with Byte 1 = 01 and Byte 3-10 populated with the measured curb wheel weights as described in “3.6.2.5 - Routine 0xF000 - OBS Calibration Data”.

 

b.      50% Payload

i.              Load the bed of the vehicle with weight equivalent to 50% +/- 2% of the vehicles maximum rated payload. Be careful to not overshoot the target. If the target load is exceeded, completely unload the vehicle before loading it again, do not simply remove weight until it is within the required range. 

ii.             Once the target vehicle load is acquired, measure the wheel weights of all four wheels individually.

iii.            Without adjusting the load on the vehicle, send Diagnostic Service 0x31, Routine Control, SubFunction 0x01, start Routine, Routine 0xF000 with Byte 1 = 02 and Byte 3-10 populated with the measured wheel weights as described in “3.6.2.5 - Routine 0xF000 - OBS Calibration Data”.

 

c.      90% Payload 

i.              Load the bed of the vehicle with weight equivalent to 90% +/- 2% of the vehicles maximum rated payload. Be careful to not overshoot the target. If the target load is exceeded, completely unload the vehicle before loading it again, do not simply remove weight until it is within the required range. 

ii.             Once the target vehicle load is acquired, measure the wheel weights of all four wheels individually.

iii.            Without adjusting the load on the vehicle, send Diagnostic Service 0x31, Routine Control, SubFunction 0x01, start Routine, Routine 0xF000 with Byte 1 = 03 and Byte 3-10 populated with the measured wheel weights as described in “3.6.2.5 - Routine 0xF000 - OBS Calibration Data”.

 

d.      40% Payload 

i.              Unload the bed of the vehicle with weight equivalent to 40% +/- 2% of the vehicles maximum rated payload. Prior to unloading the vehicle to 40% payload, the vehicle must have been loaded to 70% payload or greater. Be careful to not overshoot the target. If the target load is exceeded, re-load the vehicle to 70% payload or greater before trying again, do not simply add weights until it is within the required range. 

ii.             Once the target vehicle load is acquired, measure the wheel weights of all four wheels individually.

iii.            Without adjusting the load on the vehicle, send Diagnostic Service 0x31, Routine Control, SubFunction 0x01, start Routine, Routine 0xF000 with Byte 1 = 03 and Byte 3-10 populated with the measured wheel weights as described in “3.6.2.5 - Routine 0xF000 - OBS Calibration Data”.</ENTRY_CONDITIONS>
